arez

Class Flags

  • java.lang.Object
    • arez.Flags

  • public final class Flags
extends Object
    Flags that can be passed when creating observers that determine the configuration of the observer. The class also contains constants and methods used to extract runtime state from Observers.

      • RUN_NOW

        public static final int RUN_NOW
        The scheduler will be triggered when the observer is created to immediately invoke the Observer._observed function. This configuration should not be specified if there is no Observer._observed function supplied. This should not be specified if RUN_LATER is specified.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • RUN_LATER

        public static final int RUN_LATER
        The scheduler will not be triggered when the observer is created. The observer either has no Observer._observed function or is responsible for ensuring that ArezContext.triggerScheduler() is invoked at a later time. This should not be specified if RUN_NOW is specified.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • KEEPALIVE

        public static final int KEEPALIVE
        The runtime will keep the observer reacting to dependencies until disposed. This is the default value for observers that supply a observed function but may be explicitly supplied when creating ComputedValue instances.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PRIORITY_HIGHEST

        public static final int PRIORITY_HIGHEST
        Highest priority. This priority should be used when the observer will dispose or release other reactive elements (and thus remove elements from being scheduled).

        Only one of the PRIORITY_* flags should be applied to observer.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PRIORITY_HIGH

        public static final int PRIORITY_HIGH
        High priority. To reduce the chance that downstream elements will react multiple times within a single reaction round, this priority should be used when the observer may trigger many downstream reactions.

        Only one of the PRIORITY_* flags should be applied to observer.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PRIORITY_NORMAL

        public static final int PRIORITY_NORMAL
        Normal priority if no other priority otherwise specified.

        Only one of the PRIORITY_* flags should be applied to observer.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PRIORITY_LOW

        public static final int PRIORITY_LOW
        Low priority. Usually used to schedule observers that reflect state onto non-reactive application components. i.e. Observers that are used to build html views, perform network operations etc. These reactions are often at low priority to avoid recalculation of dependencies (i.e. ComputedValues) triggering this reaction multiple times within a single reaction round.

        Only one of the PRIORITY_* flags should be applied to observer.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PRIORITY_LOWEST

        public static final int PRIORITY_LOWEST
        Lowest priority. Use this priority if the observer is a ComputedValue that may be unobserved when a PRIORITY_LOW observer reacts. This is used to avoid recomputing state that is likely to either be unobserved or recomputed as part of another observers reaction.

        Only one of the PRIORITY_* flags should be applied to observer.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
